The paper discusses a system that makes R programs I/O-efficient, which involves database-related optimizations. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions numerical computation and inter-operation optimizations, which are related to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and Software Engineering (cs.SE).
